Roughhouse Annie on me now, huh?

721
00:50:39,297 --> 00:50:42,501
Yeah, I heard tell about you.
All talkin' and no listenin'.

722
00:50:43,167 --> 00:50:46,368
We're here trying to understand each
other for once and stop fighting.

723
00:50:46,370 --> 00:50:49,038
I'll stop fightin' when there
ain't nothing left to fight for.

724
00:50:49,040 --> 00:50:51,442
Then you gonna be goin' uphill
the rest of your life, Ann.

725
00:50:52,476 --> 00:50:55,244
In the meantime,
I'm-a keep that man here talkin'

726
00:50:55,246 --> 00:50:56,982
as long as I possibly can.

727
00:50:59,450 --> 00:51:01,419
C.P.

728
00:51:02,721 --> 00:51:03,755
C.P.

729
00:51:06,290 --> 00:51:08,858
This, um,
display you want to bring.

730
00:51:08,860 --> 00:51:10,827
We're willing to go along
with it.

731
00:51:10,829 --> 00:51:12,562
But there'll be folks not wild
about the sight of it.

732
00:51:12,564 --> 00:51:14,764
So, uh, you're gonna need
to provide some security,

733
00:51:14,766 --> 00:51:16,700
someone to watch over it.

734
00:51:16,702 --> 00:51:18,203
I'm not gonna be responsible for it.

735
00:51:21,074 --> 00:51:22,541
This is my security.

736
00:51:23,375 --> 00:51:24,978
That gun
don't belong here.

737
00:51:25,677 --> 00:51:29,448
I like to have it close in case I
need it to do my talkin' for me.

738
00:51:30,783 --> 00:51:32,918
This here does the talkin'
for me.

739
00:51:33,150 --> 00:51:36,753
- I have a Bible.
- Oh, you do? Have you read it?

740
00:51:36,755 --> 00:51:38,122
Course I've read it.

741
00:51:38,590 --> 00:51:40,957
- Even go to church on Sundays.
- Hmm.

742
00:51:40,959 --> 00:51:43,026
Well, then,
you ought to know, C.P.

743
00:51:43,028 --> 00:51:44,062
Know what?

744
00:51:44,963 --> 00:51:47,599
Same God made you, made me.

745
00:52:09,354 --> 00:52:10,788
That's everything,
Mr. Ellis.

746
00:52:10,790 --> 00:52:12,592
Looks good, Ben. Real good.

747
00:52:12,892 --> 00:52:14,494
Thank you, Mr. Ellis.

748
00:52:25,604 --> 00:52:27,806
Divided according to race.

749
00:52:29,008 --> 00:52:31,243
Uh, six black, six white.

750
00:52:31,610 --> 00:52:34,444
The senate members will float in
and out of different working groups,

751
00:52:34,446 --> 00:52:36,281
observing and participating.

752
00:52:36,849 --> 00:52:38,783
On the final night
of the charrette,

753
00:52:38,785 --> 00:52:40,951
you will vote
to either adopt or reject

754
00:52:40,953 --> 00:52:42,620
the resolutions
presented to you.

755
00:52:42,622 --> 00:52:44,356
So, we're the final word?

756
00:52:44,624 --> 00:52:46,189
Final word, Howard.

757
00:52:46,191 --> 00:52:48,494
Two-thirds majority
to pass each resolution.

758
00:52:50,263 --> 00:52:51,698
Eight votes to pass?

759
00:52:52,832 --> 00:52:55,599
Then we should be able to handpick
the other four white members.

760
00:52:55,601 --> 00:52:57,768
Well, then, we might as well
go on home then.

761
00:52:57,770 --> 00:52:59,403
C.P.,
that's not practical.

762
00:52:59,405 --> 00:53:00,840
We need to be
as fair as possible.

763
00:53:01,141 --> 00:53:03,741
I'm gonna have to side
with my friend here.

764
00:53:03,743 --> 00:53:06,178
I mean,
we can surely all agree

765
00:53:06,180 --> 00:53:08,146
that every Negro
in the building

766
00:53:08,148 --> 00:53:10,014
is gonna vote yes
on school integration.

767
00:53:10,016 --> 00:53:12,149
That's six automatic votes,
no matter what.

768
00:53:12,151 --> 00:53:14,151
Same's not true
for every last white person.

769
00:53:14,153 --> 00:53:16,321
There's a bunch of liberals
sittin' out there right now.

770
00:53:18,291 --> 00:53:22,194
Look, there are four prominent
organizations represented

771
00:53:22,196 --> 00:53:23,994
in this room, right here.

772
00:53:23,996 --> 00:53:26,464
The Klan,
The White Citizens' Council,

773
00:53:26,466 --> 00:53:28,868
Black Solidarity Committee,
and Operation Breakthrough.

774
00:53:29,635 --> 00:53:30,938
You each get your votes.

775
00:53:31,370 --> 00:53:32,538
You want fair?

776
00:53:32,906 --> 00:53:34,808
We'll pick
eight regular members.

777
00:53:35,209 --> 00:53:38,611
Regular. No black power people, no Klan.
They're excluded.

778
00:53:39,747 --> 00:53:40,781
Agreed?

779
00:53:45,085 --> 00:53:46,918
- None of her people?
- No.

780
00:53:46,920 --> 00:53:48,422
And none of y'all.

781
00:54:04,704 --> 00:54:05,738
Hey!

782
00:54:06,372 --> 00:54:08,608
What do you think
you doing, huh?

783
00:54:10,878 --> 00:54:12,744
Leave that alone.

784
00:54:12,746 --> 00:54:15,281
Boys need to be reading this
instead of ripping it up.

785
00:54:16,083 --> 00:54:20,754
The Klan is givin' you
a window to look through.

786
00:54:23,190 --> 00:54:25,224
You need to read this stuff
and understand it.

787
00:54:25,226 --> 00:54:26,693
That way,
you understand them.

788
00:54:27,027 --> 00:54:30,562
Okay? You got the upper hand.
Got it?

789
00:54:30,564 --> 00:54:32,934
Get on outta here, Charles.
Give me that.

790
00:54:33,734 --> 00:54:35,937
Should tell your daddy.
You know better.

791
00:54:44,145 --> 00:54:45,879
Kids don't make no sense...

792
00:55:17,111 --> 00:55:21,080
"...professional experts from in
the community and from outside

793
00:55:21,082 --> 00:55:23,983
will stand by
listening, learning."

794
00:55:50,945 --> 00:55:52,612
- Ann? Ann?
- What?

795
00:55:52,614 --> 00:55:54,649
- Where are you going?
- I'm going home.

796
00:55:55,450 --> 00:55:57,183
Look,
I know you're upset, Ann.

797
00:55:57,185 --> 00:55:58,718
You don't know nothing!

798
00:55:58,720 --> 00:56:00,320
I told you
it was a damn fool idea

799
00:56:00,322 --> 00:56:02,289
to let that man
bring that stuff in here.

800
00:56:02,291 --> 00:56:04,059
Ain't no good
gonna come from it!

801
00:56:04,459 --> 00:56:06,728
And I'll tell you
something else, Bill Riddick.

802
00:56:07,329 --> 00:56:08,761
You an even bigger fool

803
00:56:08,763 --> 00:56:10,396
if you think you gonna make
any change

804
00:56:10,398 --> 00:56:11,865
with this here meeting.

805
00:56:11,867 --> 00:56:13,202
- Is that right?
- That's right.

806
00:56:13,769 --> 00:56:16,236
'Cause as long as
the C.P. Ellises of the world

807
00:56:16,238 --> 00:56:17,571
keep gettin' their way,

808
00:56:17,573 --> 00:56:19,072
ain't nothing gonna change.

809
00:56:19,074 --> 00:56:21,376
Yeah, you talk about
Roughhouse Annie?

810
00:56:22,343 --> 00:56:25,177
Keep Uncle Tommin'
that cracker

811
00:56:25,179 --> 00:56:27,349
and you gonna see
Roughhouse Annie.

812
00:56:28,416 --> 00:56:31,419
Go on back up north where you belong,
'cause you don't know nothing.

813
00:57:04,753 --> 00:57:05,955
Marion Wilson.

814
00:57:13,661 --> 00:57:15,798
Okay. The other bowl now.

815
00:57:18,834 --> 00:57:19,868
<i>Sam Watford.</i>

816
00:57:21,570 --> 00:57:23,472
- Is that Scooter Watford's boy?
- Yeah.

817
00:57:24,974 --> 00:57:26,575
You won't have
a problem there.

818
00:57:27,309 --> 00:57:28,911
- You sure?
- Pretty sure.

819
00:57:29,279 --> 00:57:32,045
I remember he kept losin' jobs
during them boycotts.

820
00:57:32,047 --> 00:57:33,416
Still pretty sore about it.

821
00:57:34,451 --> 00:57:36,752
I don't like that mustache,
tell you what.

822
00:57:37,120 --> 00:57:39,055
All right. Earl Weeks.

823
00:57:41,124 --> 00:57:42,491
He's... He's with us.

824
00:57:42,758 --> 00:57:44,027
How do you know?

825
00:57:44,828 --> 00:57:46,963
He been a deacon at my church
since I was a kid.

826
00:57:47,464 --> 00:57:48,732
He don't like nobody.

827
00:57:50,200 --> 00:57:53,468
- That's a good man.
- Two for two.

828
00:57:53,470 --> 00:57:57,104
Okay, we gonna have an issue
with this gal Maddy Mays.

829
00:57:57,106 --> 00:57:58,772
The blonde over by the window.

830
00:57:58,774 --> 00:58:00,140
Yeah, she's a nurse.

831
00:58:00,142 --> 00:58:01,643
Yeah, over at Durham Clinic.

832
00:58:02,111 --> 00:58:04,680
Real "people person." I think
that's one to worry about.

833
00:58:06,416 --> 00:58:07,914
Last is Lee Trombley.

834
00:58:07,916 --> 00:58:10,318
Trombley Hardware.

835
00:58:10,320 --> 00:58:11,421
Off of Route Nine.

836
00:58:12,355 --> 00:58:14,222
What do we know?

837
00:58:14,224 --> 00:58:15,825
I don't know 'bout him, C.P.

838
00:58:16,793 --> 00:58:17,894
<i>Might be a problem there.</i>

839
00:58:18,828 --> 00:58:20,897
<i>He took over
after his daddy passed.</i>

840
00:58:21,798 --> 00:58:24,234
<i>Family man, two kids, I think.</i>

841
00:58:24,567 --> 00:58:25,835
<i>And?</i>

842
00:58:26,703 --> 00:58:28,936
<i>Everybody that
works for him is a nigger.</i>

843
00:58:28,938 --> 00:58:29,973
<i>Every one.</i>

844
00:58:30,474 --> 00:58:32,510
And they all thick as thieves.

845
00:58:36,780 --> 00:58:40,051
All right, I guess it's time we
get acquainted with Lee Trombley.

846
00:59:01,805 --> 00:59:02,906
Can I help you, sir?

847
00:59:03,973 --> 00:59:06,243
Uh... Lee around?

848
00:59:06,576 --> 00:59:09,244
No, sir. He's not here right now.
But I'm the manager.

849
00:59:09,246 --> 00:59:10,548
Something I can help you with?

850
00:59:13,184 --> 00:59:14,552
Uh, no. Um...

851
00:59:15,386 --> 00:59:16,987
I'll come back another time.

852
00:59:28,467 --> 00:59:29,534
Okay.

853
00:59:30,034 --> 00:59:32,735
Any thoughts, uh, insights?

854
00:59:33,703 --> 00:59:35,406
You don't have to
raise your hand, Maddy.

855
00:59:35,705 --> 00:59:38,108
I think it's nice to see
people talking for once.

856
00:59:38,542 --> 00:59:40,411
That ain't talkin'.
It's yellin'.

857
00:59:40,777 --> 00:59:42,677
Well, okay. It's arguing.

858
00:59:42,679 --> 00:59:45,981
But people are listening to one another.
They really are.

859
00:59:45,983 --> 00:59:49,750
They're arguing.
I've been listening to it for days,

860
00:59:49,752 --> 00:59:52,788
and still no one's answered how
integration's gonna help my kids.

861
00:59:52,790 --> 00:59:55,958
- It sure can't hurt 'em.
- It sure as hell can.

862
00:59:55,960 --> 00:59:58,961
- I'd like to know how.
- Well, for one,

863
00:59:58,963 --> 01:00:01,932
I don't want my daughter sitting
next to a Negro boy in class.

864
01:00:02,366 --> 01:00:04,099
I don't want her
eatin' next to one,

865
01:00:04,101 --> 01:00:06,269
and don't want her being
at a school dance with one.

866
01:00:06,271 --> 01:00:08,607
So, you care
about your daughter?

867
01:00:09,740 --> 01:00:11,640
And you don't want
to see her get hurt.

868
01:00:11,642 --> 01:00:13,309
What's your point?

869
01:00:13,311 --> 01:00:17,282
My point is that is
what we do as parents.

870
01:00:18,283 --> 01:00:22,184
When they're little, we try to
keep them from touching the stove

871
01:00:22,186 --> 01:00:23,387
so they don't burn.

872
01:00:24,321 --> 01:00:27,558
We teach them to take small
bites so they don't choke.

873
01:00:28,359 --> 01:00:30,993
We worry about
their first day at school,

874
01:00:30,995 --> 01:00:32,495
the first time
they drive a car,

875
01:00:32,497 --> 01:00:34,263
their very first job.

876
01:00:34,265 --> 01:00:39,067
See, we want them to avoid
the pain that we experienced.

877
01:00:39,069 --> 01:00:41,038
All right. All right.

878
01:00:41,339 --> 01:00:43,939
We all gonna sit around,
hold hands, sing "Kumbaya"?

879
01:00:43,941 --> 01:00:46,842
- We see what you're doing, Howard.
- And what is that, C.P.?

880
01:00:46,844 --> 01:00:49,179
That there's no difference
between blacks and whites, right?

881
01:00:49,181 --> 01:00:51,814
'Cause we all worry
about our kids.

882
01:00:51,816 --> 01:00:53,650
We're all the same, right?

883
01:00:53,652 --> 01:00:58,555
Actually, no, C.P. We're not.

884
01:00:58,557 --> 01:01:00,425
See, I left some things out.

885
01:01:01,159 --> 01:01:03,693
I left out
that black folks have

886
01:01:03,695 --> 01:01:06,698
a whole different menu of pain
to worry about.

887
01:01:07,832 --> 01:01:10,669
Our kids get spit on
for no reason.

888
01:01:11,503 --> 01:01:16,374
Our kids have to move on the
sidewalk to let white folks pass,

889
01:01:17,008 --> 01:01:18,343
or they get beat.

890
01:01:19,411 --> 01:01:21,779
Our kids aren't allowed
to sit where they want,

891
01:01:22,214 --> 01:01:25,684
play where they want,
go to school where they want.

892
01:01:26,818 --> 01:01:31,187
See, this is the pain
they experience every day

893
01:01:31,189 --> 01:01:34,759
that we, we can't...
can't spare them from.

894
01:01:36,462 --> 01:01:39,164
And that is a...

895
01:01:41,400 --> 01:01:42,901
It's a helpless feeling.

896
01:01:44,503 --> 01:01:47,540
A more helpless feeling
than you could ever know.

897
01:01:57,015 --> 01:01:59,349
- I fell right into that one.
- Yeah.

898
01:01:59,351 --> 01:02:01,953
- Shit. You see Trombley's face?
- Yeah.

899
01:02:02,688 --> 01:02:05,888
- Did you get anywhere with Trombley last night?
- He wasn't there.

900
01:02:05,890 --> 01:02:08,226
They were right, though.
He got a black manager.

901
01:02:08,893 --> 01:02:10,762
Well, where we gonna
get him, then?

902
01:02:11,196 --> 01:02:13,330
Right now.
We gonna crowd him at lunch.

903
01:02:13,332 --> 01:02:14,764
Mmm.

904
01:02:14,766 --> 01:02:16,736
Okay.
Everybody listen up.

905
01:02:17,902 --> 01:02:19,771
We're going to be trying
something different today.

906
01:02:20,172 --> 01:02:23,142
There are name cards at
each seat in this lunchroom.

907
01:02:23,542 --> 01:02:26,210
This will be your seat
for the rest of the charrette.

908
01:02:26,212 --> 01:02:28,281
You may not move
your name card.

909
01:02:29,282 --> 01:02:31,782
And you guessed it,
the person sitting next to you

910
01:02:31,784 --> 01:02:33,484
will not be
the same color as you.

911
01:02:33,486 --> 01:02:35,219
- What?
- And...

912
01:02:35,221 --> 01:02:39,056
And no discussion of issues
during this hour.

913
01:02:39,058 --> 01:02:40,293
Talk about something else.

914
01:04:06,714 --> 01:04:08,246
I just can't do it. Mm-mm.

915
01:04:08,248 --> 01:04:10,818
Mm-mm! Mm-mm-mm.

916
01:04:12,018 --> 01:04:14,087
These fish sticks is dry.

917
01:04:20,627 --> 01:04:22,095
Well... Hmm.

918
01:04:22,829 --> 01:04:24,765
If we can't change
anything else,

919
01:04:25,165 --> 01:04:27,634
we can sure demand
better school lunches, huh?

920
01:04:28,201 --> 01:04:30,103
We're not supposed to
talk about issues.

921
01:04:32,072 --> 01:04:33,473
I guess you're right.

922
01:04:40,213 --> 01:04:41,248
Howard...

923
01:04:42,048 --> 01:04:44,050
Howard was wrong in there,
weren't he?

924
01:04:44,752 --> 01:04:46,587
- Wrong?
- Mm-hmm.

925
01:04:48,256 --> 01:04:52,924
Well, I mean, he weren't wrong
about what black kids go through.

926
01:04:52,926 --> 01:04:53,960
But...

927
01:04:55,430 --> 01:05:00,301
He was wrong about you not knowing
what helpless is, weren't he?

928
01:05:03,772 --> 01:05:04,972
What does that mean?

929
01:05:09,142 --> 01:05:11,478
You got a boy out at Murdock,
don't you, C.P.?

930
01:05:11,913 --> 01:05:13,913
- I don't wanna talk about that.
- I'm just trying...

931
01:05:13,915 --> 01:05:16,584
Ann, don't talk about my son.

932
01:05:18,218 --> 01:05:20,455
- Don't ever talk about my son.
- Okay.

933
01:05:47,583 --> 01:05:49,916
We're willing to go
to summer school,

934
01:05:49,918 --> 01:05:52,151
even nights, just to catch
up with the white students.

935
01:05:52,153 --> 01:05:55,290
Good Lord never intended for
blacks to have equal rights.

936
01:07:11,000 --> 01:07:13,768
- Daddy!
- What's wrong? What's wrong, sugar?

937
01:07:13,770 --> 01:07:14,804
It's Larry.

938
01:07:25,848 --> 01:07:28,649
What's goin' on?

939
01:07:28,651 --> 01:07:31,218
- Who is this?
- Alvin. He moved in Friday.

940
01:07:31,220 --> 01:07:34,021
Hey, hey.
Shh, shh. Shh, shh, shh.

941
01:07:36,191 --> 01:07:38,427
Hey, pumpkin.

942
01:07:39,595 --> 01:07:41,428
- Go! It's okay.
- It's okay.

943
01:07:41,430 --> 01:07:43,798
No monster.
No monster, son. No monster.

944
01:07:43,800 --> 01:07:45,432
I got your book.
I'm gonna read...

945
01:07:45,434 --> 01:07:47,100
Shh, shh, shh.
Shh, shh, shh.

946
01:07:47,102 --> 01:07:48,236
It's Vickie.

947
01:07:48,538 --> 01:07:50,236
- Read to him.
- Okay.

948
01:07:50,238 --> 01:07:52,673
- Come here, pumpkin.
- I'll be right back.

949
01:07:52,675 --> 01:07:55,378
- Vickie's gonna read to you.
- It's your sister, Vickie.

950
01:07:55,945 --> 01:07:57,145
Get him out.

951
01:08:00,850 --> 01:08:03,718
- Hey, who's in charge here?
- Can I help you, Mr. Ellis?

952
01:08:03,720 --> 01:08:05,886
No. Is there someone else
I can talk to?

953
01:08:05,888 --> 01:08:07,121
One moment.

954
01:08:07,123 --> 01:08:08,157
Hey.

955
01:08:11,996 --> 01:08:13,628
Hey.

956
01:08:13,630 --> 01:08:14,930
- I'll be right there.
- I need help.

957
01:08:14,932 --> 01:08:16,564
- No, sir. No, sir.
- I need help.

958
01:08:16,566 --> 01:08:18,232
- My son needs help.
- Step outside that door.

959
01:08:18,234 --> 01:08:20,101
- I need to get my son out of that room.
- Yes, sir.

960
01:08:20,103 --> 01:08:22,235
Step outside for a moment.

961
01:08:22,237 --> 01:08:24,572
- Now calm it down.
- I need to get my son out of that room.

962
01:08:24,574 --> 01:08:26,741
- Your son is gonna be just fine.
- He's scared.

963
01:08:26,743 --> 01:08:28,244
